  <num>42-503</num>
  <heading>Fee simple estates — Absolute or qualified.</heading>
  <text>An estate in fee simple may be either absolute or qualified, as to one and his heirs during an existing condition of things of uncertain duration.</text>
  <annotations>
    <annotation type="History" doc="Stat. 56-2-ch854" path="§1013">Mar. 3, 1901, 31 Stat. 1351, ch. 854, § 1013</annotation>
